      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">erasure25 wrote:</div><div class="orig">All spells cast by a THM are frontal AEO cone. Your range is quite far, but only party members in a cone in front of you will be cured. It doesn't matter if you are casting Sacrifice or Cure or Stoneskin. THM is frontal cone only. Same goes for all attack spells. Spells cast as a CON are AOE circular around the target. The AOE circle doesn't extend as far distance-wise as the THM cone.</div></div> <br /> <br />I shouldnt really say this because I don't want to annoy any CON's out there but I find it quite comical that some CON's have to stand right up to where the mele are to cure the party, often getting hit by AOE/Debuffs along the way. Us THM's can usually stand far enough back to avoid these things.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
